<p>World Philosophy Day is the third Thursday of November. That’s next Thursday. How will you be celebrating?<span id="more-55596"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-55597 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/unesco-world-philosophy-day-school-of-athens-2-1024x715.png" alt="" width="573" height="400" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/unesco-world-philosophy-day-school-of-athens-2-1024x715.png 1024w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/unesco-world-philosophy-day-school-of-athens-2-300x209.png 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/unesco-world-philosophy-day-school-of-athens-2-768x536.png 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/unesco-world-philosophy-day-school-of-athens-2-400x279.png 400w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/unesco-world-philosophy-day-school-of-athens-2.png 1043w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 573px) 100vw, 573px" /></p>
<p><a class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://www.unesco.org/en/days/philosophy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">World Philosophy Day</a>, created by the United Nations Educational, Scientific, and Cultural Organization (UNESCO), celebrates “the enduring value of philosophy for the development of human thought, for each culture and for each individual.”</p>
<p>If you or your department are doing anything to mark the occasion, tell us about it.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/11/14/world-philosophy-day-is-next-thursday/">World Philosophy Day is Next Thursday</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>